4. Component Specs
4.1 Header

Slim, ~64px tall
Left: logo + token ticker (clickable → contract on Solscan in new tab)
Right: "Verify" link (opens verify page)
1px bottom border Border subtle

No wallet button. No connect anything.
4.2 Hero — Next Draw
The biggest, loudest thing on the page.
Layout: Centered card, max-width ~720px desktop, full-width minus 16px gutter on mobile.
Inside:

Prize pool (estimated) — small uppercase label Text muted ("PRIZE POOL · ESTIMATED"), value massive (clamp(48px, 8vw, 96px)) in gold, mono digits, ticking up live as fees accrue. Show native (SOL or whatever the token is) with USD equivalent below in Text secondary. The "estimated" label matters — fees are pulled from PRINTR at draw time so the live number is an estimate of what we'll actually claim.
Countdown timer — equally big or bigger. MM : SS format. Text primary until 60s remaining, then gold, then red at 10s. Ticks every second with a tiny scale pulse on the seconds digit.
Eligible count — Text secondary, with the live green pulse dot. "127 wallets in the running."
Odds line — directly under count, in Text muted: "Each has 1-in-127 odds" — calculated as 1 / eligibleCount. This is THE feature that explains v1's fairness in one line.

Edge state — drawing: when timer hits 0, card transitions to "DRAWING…" state. Replace timer with loading shimmer. When result arrives (frontend detects via the next poll cycle when a new round starts and a winner appears in /api/history), animate to a winner reveal: address + prize, gold gradient sweep, then countdown resets to 15:00.
Edge state — rolled over: "No eligible holders this round — prize rolls over."
Edge state — drawing failed: "Round complete · payout pending" with a muted yellow indicator. This will resolve once the backend retries succeed.
4.3 Leaderboard
Competitive surface. People will refresh this.
Columns (desktop):
#WalletHoldingsOdds

# — order by holdings descending. Top has a tiny gold flame.
Wallet — 0xab..3344 mono, copy-on-click → toast "Copied".
Holdings — formatted percentage 1.43% plus raw token amount in Text muted below.
Odds — for v1 this is just 1 / eligibleCount, same for everyone. Display as 0.79% or 1 in 127. Since it's identical for every row, consider making this a header-level stat instead of a per-row column to avoid visual noise. [DECIDE] Recommendation: show it once at the top of the leaderboard, drop the per-row column. Then the table is just # | Wallet | Holdings.

Mobile: card list. Each card: wallet, holdings (big), rank (small).
Real-time behavior:

Frontend polls /api/state every 2–3s.
Diff the eligible list:

New wallet → row slides in from bottom with green flash
Wallet drops → row flashes red, slides out
Re-rank → use FLIP animation (swap positions smoothly, don't re-render)


Throttle re-renders to ~500ms.

Header controls:

Search box (filter by wallet prefix)
Pagination — top 50 default, "Load more" or virtual scroll

