4.7 Verify Page (/round/:id or /verify/:id)
Critical for credibility. Bare and data-heavy on purpose.
Sections:

Round summary — id, started/ended, status, prize, winner, links to claim & payout txs
Randomness —

Seed (hex), as recorded by the server at draw time
Source: crypto.randomBytes (server-side)
A short, honest note: "v1 randomness is server-side. We publish the seed and full eligible list so the math is reproducible. v2 will move randomness on-chain."


Snapshot — the eligible wallet list at draw time, in deterministic sorted order. Downloadable as CSV.
Selection walkthrough — show the math:

   seed (hex)         = 7a3f9c12d4e5...
   seed mod 127       = 42
   eligibleWallets[42] = 0xab..3344  ← winner

Verify yourself — link to a public gist with a 10-line script that takes a round id and reproduces the winner from the published seed and snapshot.

Style this page like a block explorer: dense, monospace where appropriate, no decoration. The seriousness is the design.
4.8 "How it works" page or modal
Plain-language explanation:

Eligibility: hold > 0.2% of supply
15-minute rounds
v1 odds: equal chance for every eligible wallet (1 / N)
Where the prize money comes from: PRINTR fees from the creator wallet
Randomness: server-side crypto.randomBytes. Seed and eligible list published per round so the math is reproducible. v2 will move on-chain.
What happens if you sell, no eligible holders, etc.

Keep under 600 words. Link to the verify page and the public algorithm. Be honest about the v1 randomness limitation — it's better to flag it ourselves than to have a skeptic on Twitter point it out first.

5. Interaction & Motion Details

Copy address: click any address → toast "Copied" bottom-center, 1.5s
Hover any wallet: tooltip shows holdings · last seen eligible · win history if in the indexed data
Round transition: 0.5s sequence — timer goes red → "DRAWING" shimmer → 1.5s suspense → winner card scales in with gold sweep → feed gets new entries → countdown resets. Should feel like one continuous beat, not a page reload.
Connection indicator: tiny "Live" badge in the header with the pulse dot. If polling fails repeatedly, replace with "Reconnecting…" in muted yellow.


6. Responsive Behavior
Breakpoints:

< 640px — mobile, single column, hero compacts (timer and pool stack), leaderboard becomes card list
640–1024px — tablet, hero stays prominent, leaderboard and activity stack vertically
> 1024px — desktop, two-column leaderboard + activity, full hero

The hero must be fully visible above the fold on a 375px-wide phone. Test on iPhone SE size first.

7. Empty & Error States

No data yet (first launch) — leaderboard: "No eligible holders yet — be the first to qualify by holding 0.2% of supply." Activity feed: "Waiting for the first event…"
Polling fails — fall back to slower retry (10s, then 30s). Show muted yellow "Reconnecting" indicator.
API down entirely — full-page error: "We're having trouble loading the data. The smart contract is unaffected. Try again in a moment." Retry button.
Round void — hero says "No eligible holders this round — prize rolls over." Activity feed gets round_void entry.


8. Accessibility

Color contrast meets WCAG AA on all text. Verify each gold/dark combination.
Keyboard-reachable interactions, visible focus rings (2px gold offset).
Screen reader: countdown announced every minute (not every second); winner announcement uses aria-live="polite".
prefers-reduced-motion — pulses off, counter-ups instant, transitions become opacity fades.
Text resizable to 200% without breaking layout.
Don't rely on color alone — every green/red event has an icon too.


9. Performance Budget

Initial JS bundle under 200KB gzipped on the landing route. Code-split the verify page.
First Contentful Paint < 1.5s on a mid-tier mobile.
Lighthouse perf score ≥ 90.
Polling cadence: /api/state every 2–3s, /api/activity every 5s, /api/stats every 30s. Pause polling when tab is hidden (document.visibilityState).
Use requestAnimationFrame for the countdown, not setInterval.


10. Tech Suggestions ([DECIDE])

Framework: Next.js (App Router) or Vite + React. Next.js is helpful if you want SSR for the verify page so it indexes nicely.
Styling: Tailwind CSS. Set up the palette as CSS vars + Tailwind theme extensions.
State: React Query (or SWR) handles all the polling cleanly with built-in retry and stale-while-revalidate. Native useState for the rest.
Animation: Framer Motion for FLIP reorder + countdown pulses. Don't overuse it.
Number formatting: Intl.NumberFormat, plus a counter-up hook for animated changes.


11. Copy Tone

Confident, terse, slightly degen but never exclusionary
"Hold to win" not "Participate in our innovative reward distribution mechanism"
Numbers do most of the talking — copy gets out of the way
Use the project token's ticker, not "the token", everywhere
Never say "guaranteed". "Drawn every 15 minutes" is fine; "guaranteed payout" is not

Examples:

✅ "Hold 0.2% of supply. Win every 15 minutes."
✅ "Sell before the draw and you're out."
❌ "Join the most innovative reward ecosystem on Solana."
❌ "Earn passive income with our revolutionary protocol."


